rComments: He rants for too long off topic. He words his questions in confusing ways and I has way too many readings. He’s one of those profs that acts like he’s the only class you have.
teacherRatingTags: ['Test heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'So many papers']

rComments: Super boring lectures but super easy class. He seems like a super caring guy who tries to make lectures more interesting with humour but the subject is so dry. One of the easiest classes I've ever taken.

lectures are so boring and often have so much unnecessary information that will not be used on tests and assignments. super easy marker and really caring about his students success, just really hard to pay attention and want to attend class because of the lectures.
He genuinely care for his students, and tries to make the lectures fun. I found the course interesting and as long as you pay attention it is a really easy A.

I didn't go to a single full lecture because they were so boring and he ranted about useless things half the time. The quizzes are open book. The directives for the assignments are very unclear but he is an easy marker so it didn't really matter that much. Overall a really weird guy, but easy A

Professor Benoit is so great! His assignments are fair, exams are easy to prepare for, feedback is always super useful, and he/his classes are funny. He is always willing to help you with the assignments and provides practice quizzes to prepare you for the exams. He also provides toolbox resources that are quite interesting. Highly recommend LB!

Overall an easier grader and exams are straightforward. However lectures are boring and often all over the place, and somehow always end up just being him bragging about his accomplishments. Beware, problems that he or you have will be blamed on everyone but himself, so be careful about bringing up grading or technical issues.
I loved this teacher he was so caring! he loves his students and it shows through the class which is nice. He is also hilarious and tells funny and interesting stories.
Learned a lot in his classes. Great teacher. Very kind. Relates course content to real life experiences.

This prof is amazing! He is so funny and so caring with students. He makes sure everyone understands and is always available to answer questions! He makes practice quizzes to get familiar with the material and prepare for the exam which I loved! His class is practical and you actually learn real life scenarios to help in the future!

One of the most hostile profs I've ever had in my 4.5 years of university. I skipped 1 class & let him know IN ADVANCE, IN PERSON, and he started acting very hostile towards me, including YELLING at me. He also made uncomfortable comments on the #metoo movement and on how the international students might have problems with presentations. THE WORST.

Professor Benoit's expectations are very clear! He also presented insightful personal stories to relate to the course which shows how passionate he is about crisis communication. Although online learning has been a challenge, he was very understanding of the situation and tried his best to engage students in discussions!

All exams and assignments closely reflect powerpoint and readings. If you need help and send him an email, expect a speedy reply with a precise answer. He relates course content to real world experiences. You can tell he really loves crisis communication and enjoys teaching it. Very kind prof who wants his students to do well.

Thinks he is hilarious and loves the sound of his own voice. You will be scrambling to understand the point of his run-on sentences. Final examtake home paper worth 50%, but he didn't teach us the hardest part. Loves to make an example of students and might bight your head off for legitimate question. Very condescending in 'roundtable' assignments
Very belittling and doesnt seem to really care how you do in your class. If you dont give him exactly the answer hes looking for youre wrong

Probably my favorite teacher ever so far. He works at an executive level, so you can tell he has no patience for immature students. If you spend his lectures browsing Facebook on your laptop, he WILL notice and will be very reluctant to help you after that. If you participate and put in the effort, you will absolutely pass. Loved his class.

Difficult to learn in his class, because: his PPT have no guidelines, he talks about his personal life, does'nt answer questions, if he answers your questions good luck to understand his answer. Pretty intimidating (always had trouble to look him in the eyes). If he likes you, he will help you. NOT good at teaching at all !

Here's the thing, if you are a good student (from his perspective) he will be an excellent teacher to you, if he spots you as a careless and untalented student he might not only ignore you, but also give you the push you need to drop the class. Sometimes unethical.. his teaching skills could be improved but I have to say I learned a lot with him.
Just rambles about personal stories and yells at you for not understanding questions he asks that he doesn't teach. Avoid him.
had the worst experience taking his comms class, he was very rude and unwilling to help his students succeed.
possibly the rudest professor i've ever had. makes very inappropriate comments and is generally condescending :/

One of the few classes I've taken where I felt I'm actually able to relate and apply the material to the real world. Highly recommend his crisis communications class. He wants to make sure you succeed and helps guides students.

He's a good prof... he knows what he's talking about and really cares for his students. He can be a little intimidating at times however, and midterms aren't the easiest. All in all, don't expect an easy A in this class.
He is an amazing professor! He knows his stuff and always makes lectures interesting and fun! He's hilarious, and genuinely cares about his students and wants them to succeed. HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!

This class was an elective after history of film was full. This is one of the best classes Ive taken. The professor is super passionate and the three hour lectures go like a breeze. The readings are important and you must read them to do well in the class.

Great prof. Super passionate and keeps the lectures very interesting. Tons of case study analysis. Do the readings as he talks about them a lot in class and appreciates participation in the class discussions.

This professor is very passionate. His lectures and power point slides are quite clear. Exams are fair. For those going into the PR field, I find this class gives insight as to what to expect in the public relations world.
